Modu Afuno, a Borno State government pensioner on Tuesday night died mysteriously within a premises adjacent the state pension board. According to his fellow pensioners who lives at the pension board premises, the late Modu, a retiree of the General Hospital, Monguno, reportedly died at about 10pm at over 80 years of age. When LEADERSHIP visited the pension board late Wednesday afternoon, Modu’s corpse was being prepared for interment according to Islamic rights. The body was later lifted to a waiting pickup from where other pensioners moved with it the burial ground. A Senior Staff of the pension board who spoke on the condition of anonymity confirmed that the late Modu has a file with the board and that he has been receiving his pension regularly. A fellow aged pensioner, Modu Aminami, told newsmen: “Modu was well before his death because we didn’t know him with any ailment. “He used to sleep over the last 10 years at the old Nitel premises; we never knew him with any wife or son; he received his pension regularly and spent it alone,” he said. The pensioners said after Modu Afuno’s death, his known relations in Jos and Kaduna were notified and they gave their consent for his immediate burial in Maiduguri.